, 234, pp. 468-470; Russell, F.S., A summary of observations on the occurrence of planktonic stages of fish off Plymouth 1924-1972 (1973) J Mar Biol Assoc UK, 53, pp. 347-355; Schneider, S.H., What is 'dangerous' climate change? (2001) Nature, 411, pp. 17-19; Sims, D.W., Genner, M.J., Southward, A.J., Hawkins, S.J., Timing of squid migration reflects North Atlantic climate variability (2001) Proc R Soc Lond B, 268, pp. 1-6; Skud, B.E., Dominance in fishes: The relation between environment and abundance (1982) Science, 216, pp. 144-149; Southward, A.J., The distribution of some plankton animals in the English Channel and Western approaches. III. Theories about long term biological changes, including fish (1963) J Mar Biol Assoc UK, 43, pp. 1-29; Southward, A.J., Recent changes in abundance of intertidal barnacles in south-west England, a possible effect of climatic deterioration (1967) J Mar Biol Assoc UK, 47, pp. 81-95; Southward, A.J., The western English Channel. An inconstant ecosystem? (1980) Nature, 285, pp. 361-366; Southward, A.J., Fluctuations in the ecosystem of the western English Channel: A summary of studies in progress (1983) Proceedings of the 17th European Symposium on Marine Biology, Oceanologica Acta, SPEC. VOL., pp. 187-89; Southward, A.J., Fluctuations in the 'indicator' chaetognaths Sagitta elegans and Sagitta setosa in the western Channel (1984) Oceanol Acta, 7, pp. 229-239; Southward, A.J., Forty years changes in species composition and population density of barnacles on a rocky shore near Plymouth (1991) J Mar Biol Assoc UK, 71, pp. 3495-3513; Southward, A.J., The importance of long time-series in understanding the variability of natural systems (1995) Helgol Meeresunters, 49, pp. 329-333; Southward, A.J., Boalch, G.T., Aspects of long term changes in the ecosystem of the western English Channel in relation to fish populations (1989) Long term changes in marine fish populations, , T. Wyatt, & M.G. Larraneta. Vigo: Instituta Investigaciones Mar